				\begin{document}$$\nabla T\approx 0$$\end{document}) over a wide range of I (0 < I < 320 kW/cm2). These data are also available in the Supplement. This is reasonable since crystalline silicon has an increasingly smaller optical absorption at wavelengths (λ > 800 nm) and a good thermal conductivity. Thus, we verified that the present MFBS-assisted optical trapping is completely free from thermal effects which are detrimental for a stable trapping.
